Dow Inc., Pfizer share losses lead Dow's 29-point drop

Shares of Dow Inc. and Pfizer are seeing declines Friday morning, sending the Dow Jones Industrial Average into negative territory. The Dow DJIA, +0.52% was most recently trading 29 points (0.1%) lower, as shares of Dow Inc. DOW, +2.36% and Pfizer PFE, -0.48% have contributed to the blue-chip gauge's intraday decline. Dow Inc.'s shares are off $1.71 (3.4%) while those of Pfizer have fallen $0.68, or 1.7%, combining for an approximately 16-point drag on the Dow. Other components contributing significantly to the decline include JPMorgan Chase JPM, +0.65%, Merck MRK, -0.38%, and Goldman Sachs GS, +0.09%. A $1 move in any one of the 30 components of the index results in a 6.78-point swing.